## 3. Database Schema

### `articles` Table
Stores raw and processed articles collected from RSS feeds.
* `id` (INTEGER, Primary Key): Unique auto-increment ID.
* `title` (VARCHAR): Article headline.
* `source` (VARCHAR): Feed origin (e.g., *BBC News*, *CNBC*).
* `url` (VARCHAR): Absolute link to original article.
* `url_hash` (VARCHAR, Unique): MD5 hash of URL to avoid raw link duplication.
* `description` (TEXT): Brief summary excerpt from the XML feed.
* `content` (TEXT): High-quality 100-150 word summary generated by LLM.
* `published_date` (DATETIME): Time when the article was published.
* `is_duplicate` (BOOLEAN): Flag set by `analyzer.py` if a similar article is found.
* `is_processed` (BOOLEAN): Status of metadata extraction.
* `is_digested` (BOOLEAN): Flag indicating inclusion in a compiled digest.
* `click_count` (INTEGER): Total user read clicks (updated via route `/?.read=ID`).

### `digests` Table
Stores compiled historical digests delivered to users.
* `id` (INTEGER, Primary Key): Unique auto-increment ID.
* `digest_date` (DATETIME): Generation timestamp.
* `content` (TEXT): Aggregated digest content (markdown).
* `article_count` (INTEGER): Count of articles summarized.
* `is_sent` (BOOLEAN): Status of email/Telegram delivery.
* `sent_date` (DATETIME): Delivery timestamp.

